ign=left class=m><span class=title> Spawn Rate</span><hr size=1> Trak is a 72-hour spawn, roughly. Leaving him up for 48 hours is a problem.<br><br>Example:<br>Trak is reserved for Saturday at 7PM PST. Trak dies at 7PM PST. Trak is up again on Tuesday at 7PM PST.<br><br>-or-<br><br>Trak is reserved for Saturday at 7PM PST. Trak dies at 7PM on MONDAY, 48 hours after reservation. Trak isn't up again until Thursday at 7PM PST.<br><br>This 48 hour thing means Trak effectively becomes a 5 day spawn, instead of a 3-day spawn.<br><br>Realistically, you have 12 hours to kill your reserved spawn. Even that is pushing it.<br><br>Kaladur <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulordhavemercy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Have Mercy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 510<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 6:19:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=603.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://geocities.com/jd_lhm/bruchani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spawn Rate</span><hr size=1> it also means that guild that wait 6 days to kill something because they have to muster forces are gonna be screwed <p><img src="http://geocities.com/jd_lhm/chakan.jpg" border=0><BR>Chakan Sun'Tzu<BR>Master of 276 Bubbles of Orangness<BR>"it is our simplicity that makes us complex"<BR>-Bruce Li</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bluclin71335.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kaladur>Kaladur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 6:33:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.sho