5-20 linkdeaths the first time Trak AEs with that many people in range.<br><br>Of course, this tends to take care of itself as people die. But the point is, if you can't do it with 36, you prolly can't do it with 45, unless you added 9 wizzies. :P<br><br>So, anyway, don't expect to get 48 hours to kill something. That's three evenings. If you can't get it done in one evening, step aside.<br><br>Kaladur <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 7:18:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=603.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Furthermore</span><hr size=1> So make the rule different for Trak. Make it 12 hours or something like that.  At the meeting they were mostly talking about Vox and Naggy.  Someone, I believe it was Calidorn wanted there to be a 7 day wait.  I felt that was too long and objected.  If 2 days does not work for Trak, and everyone is in agreement on that, there is no reason it can't be shorter.<br><br> <p>Valas Defai</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uayukawamadoka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ayukawa Madoka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://smilecwm.tripod.com/cwm2/la.gif  BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 7:36:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=603.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Furthermore</span><hr size=1> I believe the reason the two days were alloted are because there are guilds that can't muster up the power to drop these mobs immediately. It is done to be fair to the guilds that aren't uber. It isn't fair to say &quot;you have 12 hours to drop this mob, or you are SOL&quot;. Everyone deserves a chance, even if it means waiting a little bit longer. For now, the rules are as stated, and I hope that everyone can respect that until something else can be agreed upon. This took time and patience by everyone involved, please understand that. If you have a better suggestion, bring it up at the next council meeting. Until then, please understand that these decisions were made to be fair to everyone on the server. If you want a voice in how things are done, please become an active part of this council. That is the only way things are going to stay peaceful on Luclin. I also hope to see more guilds represented at the next meeting.  <p><font color=ff0000>Ayukawa Madoka</font><BR> <img src=http://smilecwm.tripod.com/dvv/asthanos.gif> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usegalsoulsaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Segal SoulSaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 7:44:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=603.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Furthermore</span><hr size=1> You not talking about 12 hours notice, in most cases your going to have a weeks notice.  In the case of a 3-day spawn, you will have 3 days notice minimum.   Trak died last night, he will be back up again on Wednesday.  Adding 48 hours is really giving you 5 days notice.   The 7 day spawns are even easier, Naggy died last Friday, will respawn this Friday.<br><br>A fair way to do this would be to let Guild A trade spots with Guild B in case of the rare emergency server downage.  Example:  Guild A wants to do Naggy next Friday and is planning all their resources to get it done.   Boom, Server goes down on Wednesday and they are not ready.  So Guild A contacts one of the guilds on the list that could do the spawn on short notice and trades places on the list with them. <p>Segal - 60 Cleric - Luclin <br>Chachon - 50 Monk - Luclin <BR>First House of <a href="http://pub26.ezboard.com/bapex71990">APEX</a> <BR>Lord of the House of Hammers <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umaoudeib.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maoudeib</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/01 7:51:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=603.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/maobeq/maobpic5.jpg width = 120 height = 130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Number 9</span><hr size=1> Perhaps Number 9 would apply once more than a few different groups or guilds can kill that particular dragon or special mob.  Before that point, guilds that can kill a dragon can work out some type of rotation amongst themselves.  <br><br>However, groups attempting to kill the dragon or mob for the first time should definitely be given a chance to do so (48 hour grace period). Thus, make your first attempt a good one, prepare properly, ensure you have the enough people of the proper classes, gear and level.<br><br>Here's the current status of dragons and special mobs. Special quest mobs should not be placed on Calendar or given a grace period, except perhaps Ragefire.<br><br>Vox/Naggy: many guilds with members around 47-52 can kill these dragons.  Suitable for Calendar.<br><br>Kelorek'Dar: many guilds can kill this dragon, although the respawn is unknown. Not a good dragon to put on the calendar until respawn is determined.  Otherwise how can one group know if their reservation is too close to another reservation?  Once respawn is known reliably, suitable for Calendar.<br><br>Phinegel and Master Yael: many guilds can kill these mobs.  I am not aware of respawn rate, but I believe they are known.  If respawn rate is known, suitable for Calendar.<br><br>Faydedar(sp?) and Giant Turtle: many guilds can kill this mob, although respawn is unknown.  Also this mob despawns. Never suitable for Calendar.<br><br>VS: A few guilds have killed this mob so far, but I suspect other groups are capable at this time.  Possibly suitable for Calendar, but shorter grace period (24 hours?) due to long respawn (7 days confirmed).<br><br>Ragefire: special case, reservation ok but no grace period after spawn. Interested parties are expected to be ready when the spawn is up due to the time-critical nature of this mob.  <br><br>Severilous, Trakanon, Talendar: only two guilds have killed this dragon, but I suspect a third multiguild group could probably do it at this time.  Too early to put on Calendar.<br><br>Goreindaire (sp?): Nobody on Luclin has killed this bad boy yet. To early for Calendar.<br><br>Woushi: 1-2 guilds have killed this dragon so far. Too early for Calendar.<br><br>VP dragons: only one guild has entered VP so far. Too early for Calendar.<br><br>I welcome any comments on this.  However, I think it's obvious that not all major mobs and dragons can be treated the same way by the Calendar and the reservation system.<br> <p>Phantasmist Maob<BR>Lord of the House of Illusion<BR>Member of the House of Auratus<BR>Loyal to the Fi